Boil a half-full #kettle{}.

Meanwhile, heat a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).
Once hot, fry the @British Pork Mince{240%grams}, ~{5-6%minutes}. Break up the
mince as it cooks, then drain the fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash hands and utensils after handling raw meat. Cook so there's
> no pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, pour the boiling water into a #saucepan{} with @salt{1/4%tsp} on
high heat. Boil the @Basmati Rice{150%grams}, ~{10-12%minutes}. Once cooked,
drain, pop back in the pan and cover.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @Mixed Beans{1%carton}.

Add the @Tomato Puree{30%grams} to the pork. Cook, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the beans, @Red Wine Stock Paste{28%grams}, @Chipotle Paste{20%grams}
(add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Honey{1%tbsp} and
@Water{100%milliliter} for the sauce. Bring to the boil and simmer,
~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove from the heat. Add a splash of water if it's a little thick.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the pork chilli.

Drizzle over the @Soured Cream{75%grams}.

Enjoy!